  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Maintenance and Project Executive",
  "description": "<p>The Maintenance and Project Executive will play a vital frontline role in ensuring the reliability, safety, and performance of key defence infrastructure across the island.<br /><br />This is a hands-on role for individuals who enjoy problem-solving, teamwork, and making a real impact through their technical expertise.<br /></p><p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p><ul><li><p>Be part of a dedicated maintenance team providing scheduled and corrective maintenance for critical defence systems</p></li><li><p>Act as the first responder during equipment faults, attending on-site activations to restore system functionality</p></li><li><p>Support 24/7 operations through an on-call rotation (work outside office hours and on weekends will be compensated with time-off)</p></li><li><p>Handle procurement-related administrative tasks as part of project maintenance</p></li><li><p>Assist the Project Manager with project coordination, administration, and work scope execution</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimally ITE graduates in Engineering or Information & Digital Technologies. Other candidates with relevant technical skills and experience may also apply.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to provide 24/7 on-call support and work effectively in a team-based environment</p></li><li><p>Valid Class 3 driver’s license with at least 2 years of driving experience</p></li><li><p>Comfortable working at heights and in industrial environments</p></li><li><p>Reliable team player with a proactive and responsible mindset</p></li></ul><p><br />At Surbana Jurong, we put talent, hard work, teamwork and a fun workplace together to approach problems and solve them creatively and collaboratively. Join us in making a positive impact on the world!</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
